    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
      <p>Incoming letters concerning Kenney's writings; religious, ethical, and
        scientific questions; Cornell University alumni affairs; and personal and
        family matters. Also, manuscript and published copies of Kenney's
        autobiographical writings, essays, poems, and musical compositions;
        photographs; newspaper clippings, broadsides, pamphlets, programs, and other
        printed items pertaining to his literary career, Cornell, the Washington
        Secular Society, women's suffrage, national politics, and various public
        issues.</p> 
    </scopecontent> 
